  "body": {
    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<div class=\"contentLayout2\"><style>[data-colorid=x0ookzplba]{color:#4c9aff} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=x0ookzplba]{color:#004eb3}</style>\n<div class=\"columnLayout fixed-width\" data-layout=\"fixed-width\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523393/RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760482124&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=362\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/599523393/RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760482124&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"611\" data-width=\"1280\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"599523406\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"599523393\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"2\" data-media-id=\"ee70aea0-d953-4b6b-a708-5cceb1536bda\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523393/RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760482124&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1280&amp;height=611 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523393/RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760482124&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=362 1x\" /></span><p>Let's play cinematographer in Solaris and learn about Pixar's lighting toolset</p><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-information conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"690852aa-35f7-45aa-a685-b79bb73de827\" data-macro-name=\"info\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>Note: Even though these lessons are in Solaris, the theory taught here will apply to all RenderMan Lights in any DCC.</p></div></div><hr /><h1 id=\"R.F.-Lighting-LightBasics\">Light Basics</h1><p /><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"387ae1b9-5bbf-4714-bea5-ccf848b309a2\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-51051407\"><div id=\"expander-control-51051407\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Light Intensity</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-51051407\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"70d3142d-12d3-4b73-bce4-e7b8d76dff05\" data-macro-id=\"98d34443fcd0c558ca834be7a73c7cf258c18830241558c4f772145a236d810d\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/932927285\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>Discover Pixar-centric workflows for the fundamental concepts of light intensity and exposure.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"28bd4295-3987-4bb3-9eb1-0f5ad1168552\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-1635503597\"><div id=\"expander-control-1635503597\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Light Temperature</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-1635503597\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"c3bbb305-0279-45d8-bbcc-05bd858fb5e2\" data-macro-id=\"02a6c2284d8f791226f1722a0433af728ed7dcee42d526adb89543bcd05f4f90\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/932838486\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>Learn about one of the most fundamental lighting attributes for matching incandescent light color.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"a5759316-b246-486c-891f-2fad600bc5fa\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-346175216\"><div id=\"expander-control-346175216\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Normalize Light</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-346175216\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"5df0e578-cdd7-44fb-acb4-28fd2da2cd2e\" data-macro-id=\"fe783b219dcdb669d93467b0d6dc07dc5c6f64014df2f26fe123e7c890efe70a\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/944486567\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>Physics begone! Learn how to bring more artistic control to your lighting and shadows with light normalization.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"c8020527-fa00-483f-8d7a-80388178816e\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-726680083\"><div id=\"expander-control-726680083\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Diffuse &amp; Specular</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-726680083\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"a8bf7049-5ef2-4f6b-9ec0-013e7174149f\" data-macro-id=\"27c3da013fca048a5963cccfded540a2336b6c017a39e016587683ba1c4c1ae6\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/932863350\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>Break physics even more by controlling diffuse and specular light contributions separately.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"36b87635-db05-4d13-bf57-9646a42421e3\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-515621518\"><div id=\"expander-control-515621518\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Intensity Near Distance</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-515621518\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"633df180-b45c-42ac-87a4-229c6be7cf44\" data-macro-id=\"4f2451c353f616cab2dc953571256356ea26b71bc2602f4f35c53d97ca06b7da\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/932822243\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>Tired of blown-out surfaces? Pixar lights can help you attenuate the intensity by distance.</p></div></div><p /><hr /><h1 id=\"R.F.-Lighting-LightTypes\">Light Types</h1><p>Each light can be used for different effects, so let's understand its attributes</p><p /><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"455bef6a-9ab0-428d-a7bd-399626a2fdd8\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-36471350\"><div id=\"expander-control-36471350\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Dome Light</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-36471350\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"6d4692df-329c-4435-9541-f261677d1327\" data-macro-id=\"32618322e7ad4a3a530223fc50ad7d9a488add81a989d798774c022b47032f67\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/957922791\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>The dome or environment light is fundamental in every photorealistic render, so let's take a look at the basics.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"a4eb4e7f-3a1c-4267-91c7-9feac5eb05e7\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-150355162\"><div id=\"expander-control-150355162\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Rectangular Light</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-150355162\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"228a5cb7-eb4e-4867-90a8-f1a81d2699d2\" data-macro-id=\"ae265fbde69cc14624642883f17be34161ac193a8729a462ed56c64937961de8\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/932848665\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>Learn about the most popular tool in a lighter's arsenal ... the Pixar Rectangular Light.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"ef2c91e4-a9b3-4bd6-bfa8-f68b50dc8cad\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-308204865\"><div id=\"expander-control-308204865\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Cylinder Light</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-308204865\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"7a5770f2-aa0d-454f-9119-474973b532d5\" data-macro-id=\"baa744dd8a1f04f8e6d8eeef75381833272a89b225f10b50185f3a59644ec263\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/932832335\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>Strip Lights and Lightsabers have one thing in common ... Cylinder Lights!</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"50d62740-5483-4705-a35b-fa294dbb80de\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-181946570\"><div id=\"expander-control-181946570\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Sphere Lights</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-181946570\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"b6947ac6-2787-4719-b874-88174d0a9ddf\" data-macro-id=\"6b269f4c463cba23f72612d87d8a79989a63eb6307d54a1fe1ee63e74e08224f\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/932871985\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>Sometimes we need to simulate a light bulb, and Sphere Lights come to the rescue.</p></div></div><hr /><h1 id=\"R.F.-Lighting-LightFiltersBasics\">Light Filters Basics</h1><p>Learn about Light Filters ... Pixar's secret ingredient to creative lighting!</p><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"058bd0b1-c46f-4055-a939-3ee1a0d945ab\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-1607345956\"><div id=\"expander-control-1607345956\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Light Filter Basics</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-1607345956\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"a60ee935-60f1-4198-a890-750e6662fcf4\" data-macro-id=\"ff122965e696362fa58dc735e81b2dd40cbdaf952402449ed30ceab331060b2d\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/957923898\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>Eugene Riecansky introduces the great light filter toolset in Solaris.</p></div></div><p /><hr /><h3 id=\"R.F.-Lighting-NextSteps\"><span data-colorid=\"x0ookzplba\">Next Steps</span></h3><p>Ace!  Now you&rsquo;ve finished the lighting part, it&rsquo;s time to put all that knowledge into practice!</p><p>Go forth and apply all you&rsquo;ve learnt into your next render and share with us on our Discord server</p><p /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"columnLayout two-equal\" data-layout=\"two-equal\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RU/pages/599523361/R.F.+-+Patterns\" data-linked-resource-id=\"599523361\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\"><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-left-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-left\" alt=\"previousLesson.png\" width=\"200\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523393/previousLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760482125&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=200&amp;height=46\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/599523393/previousLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760482125&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"67\" data-width=\"286\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"599523409\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"previousLesson.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"599523393\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"2\" data-media-id=\"1c433f2f-37e4-41a4-a26e-7e2fbe40baa3\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523393/previousLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760482125&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=286&amp;height=67 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523393/previousLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760482125&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=200&amp;height=46 1x\" /></span></a><p /></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<p /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"columnLayout fixed-width\" data-layout=\"fixed-width\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<hr /><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"RenderManUniversity_logo_Small.png\" width=\"100\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523393/RenderManUniversity_logo_Small.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760482465&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=100&amp;height=100\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/599523393/RenderManUniversity_logo_Small.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760482465&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"100\" data-width=\"100\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"599523412\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderManUniversity_logo_Small.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"599523393\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"2\" data-media-id=\"af300b41-77ef-4608-a951-c681ab711e28\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523393/RenderManUniversity_logo_Small.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760482465&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=100&amp;height=100 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523393/RenderManUniversity_logo_Small.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760482465&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;widt